1
00:01:23,890 --> 00:01:30,090
[A Love Story: Sunshine of My Live]

2
00:01:30,090 --> 00:01:32,980
[Episode 23]

3
00:01:33,540 --> 00:01:38,080
Old Xia. You can smell osmanthus in the air.

4
00:01:40,490 --> 00:01:43,110
Old Tang, you didn't ask me over

5
00:01:43,110 --> 00:01:47,320
just to play Go and smell osmanthus, did you?

6
00:01:47,320 --> 00:01:50,000
When you are old, you think about the past.

7
00:01:50,000 --> 00:01:54,160
I have no one else but you, my old friend.

8
00:01:54,160 --> 00:01:57,740
So much happened in the past. What's on your mind?

9
00:01:57,740 --> 00:02:00,880
We didn't have a lot of money back in the day when we tried to start a company.

10
00:02:00,880 --> 00:02:05,280
Orders came in from our foreign customers and we put them together. It was hard work and not a lot of money.

11
00:02:05,280 --> 00:02:08,880
We've come a long way to Mingyuan.

12
00:02:09,900 --> 00:02:15,310
Right. It hasn't been easy.

13
00:02:15,310 --> 00:02:18,410
And I'm really grateful to you

14
00:02:18,410 --> 00:02:20,790
and Old Wei, my old friends.

15
00:02:20,790 --> 00:02:24,130
Mingyuan wouldn't be where it is without you.

16
00:02:24,130 --> 00:02:27,710
But how did we manage to get into today's predicament?

17
00:02:27,710 --> 00:02:29,780
First off,

18
00:02:30,320 --> 00:02:32,360
things are different now.

19
00:02:32,360 --> 00:02:35,410
Secondly, you are not.

20
00:02:35,410 --> 00:02:38,200
You are still so conservative.

21
00:02:39,000 --> 00:02:41,570
I don't like hearing this. What makes you think I am conservative?

22
00:02:41,570 --> 00:02:44,280
You cling on to Songtang. If you're not conservative, who is?

23
00:02:44,280 --> 00:02:47,780
I like Songtang. It's Chinoiserie.

24
00:02:47,780 --> 00:02:50,080
That's the soul of our company.

25
00:02:50,080 --> 00:02:53,160
- It's what makes us different.
- But why do we have to be different?

26
00:02:53,160 --> 00:02:57,010
- It's safer to follow the trends.
- What about our personality?

27
00:02:57,010 --> 00:03:00,900
What personality? You can barely stay afloat.

28
00:03:00,900 --> 00:03:04,390
Tang, we are not young anymore.

29
00:03:04,390 --> 00:03:08,600
Can you really look us in the eye and ask us to follow you into danger?

30
00:03:10,730 --> 00:03:12,520
Here is what I think.

31
00:03:12,520 --> 00:03:16,400
As a businessman, I'm happy to do what makes me money.

32
00:03:16,400 --> 00:03:20,660
But we also have to look beyond short-term gains.

33
00:03:20,660 --> 00:03:24,660
Right? If we can acquire SLC,

34
00:03:24,660 --> 00:03:28,520
Mingyuan will be even bigger. Everybody wins.

35
00:03:28,520 --> 00:03:30,930
Right. You are absolutely right.

36
00:03:30,930 --> 00:03:34,670
You paint me a tantalizing picture, but again, I'm an old man.

37
00:03:34,670 --> 00:03:37,690
Don't talk to me about the future.

38
00:03:37,690 --> 00:03:39,660
I don't want to think about the future.

39
00:03:39,660 --> 00:03:42,600
I, too, am a businessman. I, too, am happy to make a lot of money.

40
00:03:42,600 --> 00:03:46,000
But you know the size of Mingyuan's assets, don't you?

41
00:03:46,000 --> 00:03:47,690
Don't you?

42
00:03:47,690 --> 00:03:50,330
- Now...
- Dad. Uncle Tang.

43
00:03:50,330 --> 00:03:52,340
Aunt Lu said dinner's ready.

44
00:03:52,340 --> 00:03:55,040
Okay. Let's go.

45
00:03:56,840 --> 00:04:00,310
You think about it. Don't be whimsical.

46
00:04:00,310 --> 00:04:04,480
- I have confidence that we can do it.
- Where is the money?

47
00:04:24,820 --> 00:04:27,160
Good, very good.

48
00:04:27,160 --> 00:04:29,090
Start.

49
00:04:31,290 --> 00:04:33,440
I am looking forward to the end product.

50
00:04:33,440 --> 00:04:35,240
Yes.

51
00:04:35,240 --> 00:04:37,280
Very good.

52
00:04:38,900 --> 00:04:40,880
Let's begin.

53
00:05:10,440 --> 00:05:12,970
It is a pressing matter.

54
00:05:12,970 --> 00:05:15,460
I am wearing this

55
00:05:15,460 --> 00:05:18,720
to my daughter's wedding.

56
00:05:18,720 --> 00:05:22,060
We are extremely sorry. However, this dress

57
00:05:22,060 --> 00:05:24,800
has to be sent to the main department for it to be fixed.

58
00:05:24,800 --> 00:05:29,220
- How long would it take?
- Four days.

59
00:05:29,220 --> 00:05:33,060
No, no. I have to go tonight.

60
00:05:33,060 --> 00:05:35,000
Since the embroidery is on the sleeves,

61
00:05:35,000 --> 00:05:38,530
our embroidery frames are too big.

62
00:05:38,530 --> 00:05:42,440
Is there no other way to fix it?

63
00:05:42,440 --> 00:05:45,350
- Can I have a try?
- You have an idea?

64
00:05:45,350 --> 00:05:47,410
Yes, I have an idea.

65
00:05:47,410 --> 00:05:52,040
But I may not be able to fix it exactly the same.

66
00:06:30,440 --> 00:06:32,840
What is this technique?

67
00:06:32,840 --> 00:06:35,710
This is Chinese Suzhou Embroidery.

68
00:06:35,710 --> 00:06:38,150
A very old and ancient way of embroidery.

69
00:06:38,150 --> 00:06:40,050
Thank you. Thank you very much.

70
00:06:40,050 --> 00:06:42,340
Can I take a picture of your clothing?

71
00:06:42,340 --> 00:06:46,810
I want to keep this memory of a French Arts and

72
00:06:46,810 --> 00:06:50,650
- Chinese Skills combination.
- Of course.
- Thank you.

73
00:07:08,110 --> 00:07:10,290
I am going to tell Miya everything

74
00:07:10,290 --> 00:07:13,480
that happened today.

75
00:07:13,480 --> 00:07:18,050
Your effort today deserves great praise.

76
00:07:18,050 --> 00:07:19,800
Thank you.

77
00:07:20,740 --> 00:07:22,600
Have a look.

78
00:07:22,600 --> 00:07:24,750
This will be your studio.

79
00:07:24,750 --> 00:07:26,860
I hope you like it.

80
00:07:38,130 --> 00:07:41,170
Thank you, President Tang. I like it very much.

81
00:07:41,900 --> 00:07:45,920
I expect to see you do something great in here.

82
00:07:45,920 --> 00:07:48,130
I won't let you down.

83
00:07:48,130 --> 00:07:51,780
- I'm putting a foldaway bed right here. I'll live here.
- You can't.

84
00:07:51,780 --> 00:07:55,480
You need good rest if you want to get some good work done.

85
00:07:55,480 --> 00:07:57,250
- Mingxuan.
- Hey.

86
00:07:57,250 --> 00:07:58,640
Come here. Let me introduce you.

87
00:07:58,640 --> 00:08:02,020
This is Xia Xueling, Mingyuan's Design Director.

88
00:08:02,020 --> 00:08:05,530
- Nice to meet you, Teacher Cheng.
- Call me Cheng Yang.

89
00:08:05,530 --> 00:08:09,520
I saw your work, but never the person who created it until now.

90
00:08:10,200 --> 00:08:11,740
Welcome to Mingyuan.

91
00:08:11,740 --> 00:08:14,040
This is Liu Pei.

92
00:08:14,040 --> 00:08:17,990
- Talk to her if you need anything.
- Teacher Cheng.

93
00:08:17,990 --> 00:08:19,770
I've heard so much about you.

94
00:08:19,770 --> 00:08:21,440
Let me introduce your two assistants.

95
00:08:21,440 --> 00:08:24,840
This is Yu Xia. He joined us after the contest.

96
00:08:24,840 --> 00:08:27,570
He may be new but he is one of the best we have here.

97
00:08:27,570 --> 00:08:31,370
This is Chen Dongdong, our most valuable intern.

98
00:08:31,370 --> 00:08:33,160
They'll be working for you.

99
00:08:33,160 --> 00:08:36,480
- Teacher Cheng.
- Teacher Cheng.
- Hi.

100
00:08:36,480 --> 00:08:39,840
- I'll let you be. I have something I need to take care of in my office.

101
00:08:39,840 --> 00:08:42,460
- Okay.
- It was nice meeting you.

102
00:08:46,840 --> 00:08:49,790
Director Xia is not how I pictured her.

103
00:08:49,790 --> 00:08:52,780
How did you picture her?

104
00:08:52,780 --> 00:08:56,350
She reminds me of Elsa.

105
00:08:56,350 --> 00:08:59,650
- Who?
- You know, the Snow Queen?

106
00:09:01,050 --> 00:09:03,920
♪ Let it go! Let it go! ♪

107
00:09:03,920 --> 00:09:07,800
♪ Can't hold it back anymore. ♪

108
00:09:08,920 --> 00:09:12,310
All right, you get each other already.

109
00:09:12,310 --> 00:09:15,750
Work can wait. Please give Teacher Cheng a tour.

110
00:09:15,750 --> 00:09:17,320
Okay.

111
00:09:17,320 --> 00:09:20,320
- I'll enjoy it.
- Go get them.

112
00:09:20,320 --> 00:09:22,660
Good-bye, President Tang.

113
00:09:24,520 --> 00:09:26,540
This just came in, right?

114
00:09:28,920 --> 00:09:31,940
- P-President Tang.
- Busy?

115
00:09:31,940 --> 00:09:36,360
I was just showing her how that computer works.

116
00:09:36,360 --> 00:09:39,170
- I hope I didn't interrupt.
- Not at all.

117
00:09:39,170 --> 00:09:43,680
President Tang, it is some good news that Mr. Cheng joined us.

118
00:09:43,680 --> 00:09:46,520
This way, even if Director Xia gets busy,

119
00:09:46,520 --> 00:09:49,000
you won't be scurrying about...

120
00:09:49,000 --> 00:09:53,260
I mean we've been straining our brains for so many days now.

121
00:09:53,260 --> 00:09:56,960
Don't we deserve a break?

122
00:09:56,960 --> 00:10:00,460
- You're tired?
- No, I'm not.

123
00:10:00,460 --> 00:10:03,450
You wish you'd get to take a break, don't you?

124
00:10:03,450 --> 00:10:05,850
Get the car. We're going somewhere.

125
00:10:05,850 --> 00:10:08,490
- Where?
- The embroidery workshop.

126
00:10:29,600 --> 00:10:32,530
Here, drink some water. You haven't had a drop the whole day.

127
00:10:32,530 --> 00:10:34,080
Thank you.

128
00:10:36,410 --> 00:10:38,480
Have you made the appointment with Master Li?

129
00:10:38,480 --> 00:10:41,600
Yes. She is at the museum and will be here in no time.

130
00:10:41,600 --> 00:10:44,220
Okay. Let's have a look.

131
00:10:48,270 --> 00:10:51,080
President Tang, you look thinner.

132
00:10:51,640 --> 00:10:54,520
Yes, I've been busy.

133
00:10:54,520 --> 00:10:56,660
Mo Fei said you were in France.

134
00:10:56,660 --> 00:10:58,640
How is she?

135
00:10:58,640 --> 00:11:02,290
I haven't seen her for a while. I miss her.

136
00:11:03,450 --> 00:11:05,920
Don't worry. That girl...

137
00:11:05,920 --> 00:11:09,040
She is taking very good care of herself.

138
00:11:09,040 --> 00:11:10,920
She is just like her mom.

139
00:11:10,920 --> 00:11:13,290
Strong and independent.

140
00:11:13,290 --> 00:11:15,280
You know her mom?

141
00:11:15,280 --> 00:11:18,800
Yes. Her mom is a very busy woman.

142
00:11:18,800 --> 00:11:20,720
Travels around the world.

143
00:11:20,720 --> 00:11:22,910
She'd send her little girl here

144
00:11:22,910 --> 00:11:25,880
for winter and summer breaks.

145
00:11:25,880 --> 00:11:27,650
I was supposed to be the one looking after her.

146
00:11:27,650 --> 00:11:31,450
Instead, I had myself a little assistant.

147
00:11:31,450 --> 00:11:35,920
She took such good care of the workshop.

148
00:11:36,770 --> 00:11:40,220
I find that hard to believe.

149
00:11:40,220 --> 00:11:43,220
She is a stubborn child. No filters.

150
00:11:43,220 --> 00:11:45,400
So she can make a lot of enemies.

151
00:11:45,980 --> 00:11:49,820
President Tang, you are a few years her senior.

152
00:11:49,820 --> 00:11:53,120
I'd appreciate it if you'd put up with her temper

153
00:11:53,120 --> 00:11:55,800
and with her being in France.

154
00:11:55,800 --> 00:11:59,640
I hope you will keep an eye on her little brother.

155
00:11:59,640 --> 00:12:02,880
Don't worry. I will.

156
00:12:12,090 --> 00:12:13,760
Mo Fan.

157
00:12:14,440 --> 00:12:16,280
President Tang.

158
00:12:17,160 --> 00:12:20,300
Get in the car. I want to see how you are doing.

159
00:12:25,200 --> 00:12:26,750
Here.

160
00:12:50,160 --> 00:12:52,280
Please, come in.

161
00:13:02,240 --> 00:13:05,140
Mo Fan, sit down.

162
00:13:05,140 --> 00:13:06,970
Okay.

163
00:13:09,620 --> 00:13:11,220
Here.

164
00:13:12,530 --> 00:13:14,980
Is it... ice cream?

165
00:13:14,980 --> 00:13:16,510
Yes.

166
00:13:16,510 --> 00:13:18,820
Your sister told me

167
00:13:18,820 --> 00:13:22,120
you liked this ice cream growing up.

168
00:13:22,120 --> 00:13:24,920
Yes, I did.

169
00:13:24,920 --> 00:13:29,710
But I'm still in the middle of my training. I'm not supposed to have desserts.

170
00:13:29,710 --> 00:13:31,240
Right.

171
00:13:33,650 --> 00:13:35,360
Then I'll have one.

172
00:13:38,330 --> 00:13:41,330
- President Tang...
- Why did you call me?

173
00:13:41,330 --> 00:13:43,330
- President Tang.
- Think again.

174
00:13:45,200 --> 00:13:47,200
Brother-in-Law.

175
00:13:50,400 --> 00:13:52,810
You've been living here alone since your sister left?

176
00:13:52,810 --> 00:13:55,010
Yes. It feels lonely

177
00:13:55,010 --> 00:13:57,090
without sis.

178
00:13:57,090 --> 00:13:59,740
- You miss her.
- No, I don't.

179
00:13:59,740 --> 00:14:01,660
We fought a lot growing up. Sometimes we got physical.

180
00:14:01,660 --> 00:14:04,590
President Tang... Brother-in-law, listen.

181
00:14:04,590 --> 00:14:07,890
My sister was quite a fighter. She kicked my butt.

182
00:14:11,490 --> 00:14:13,430
That's when you were small.

183
00:14:13,430 --> 00:14:17,370
- You mustn't bully your sister anymore.
- Yes.

184
00:14:17,370 --> 00:14:20,750
Although she is a big girl and a tough fighter...

185
00:14:20,750 --> 00:14:24,680
Exactly, President Tang... Brother-in-Law.

186
00:14:25,530 --> 00:14:29,330
I'll tell your sister you said that.

187
00:14:29,330 --> 00:14:31,600
Don't, Brother-in-Law.

188
00:14:31,600 --> 00:14:34,510
I'd have to stay at your place for a few days.

189
00:14:34,510 --> 00:14:37,670
Why? You want to see Lu Zhu?

190
00:14:37,670 --> 00:14:41,710
She keeps coming to us and getting me to cook for her.

191
00:14:42,740 --> 00:14:46,820
It's okay for you to share a meal.

192
00:14:51,040 --> 00:14:53,740
It's late.

193
00:14:53,740 --> 00:14:56,090
Put this in the fridge if you are not going to eat it now.

194
00:14:56,090 --> 00:14:58,730
Okay, I will.

195
00:14:59,490 --> 00:15:03,210
You are living by yourself in Shanghai. Call me if you need anything.

196
00:15:03,210 --> 00:15:04,890
Yes.

197
00:15:06,150 --> 00:15:08,550
Take care, Brother-in-Law.

198
00:15:08,550 --> 00:15:10,990
Good boy.

199
00:15:12,120 --> 00:15:14,540
- Don't stay up too late.
- Of course. Bye.

200
00:15:14,540 --> 00:15:16,660
Bye.

201
00:15:20,900 --> 00:15:23,490
How did you find time to talk with me?

202
00:15:23,490 --> 00:15:25,190
You never reach out.

203
00:15:25,190 --> 00:15:28,540
I thought you were too busy falling in love to catch up with your friend.

204
00:15:28,540 --> 00:15:31,080
Listen to you. Am I that kind of person?

205
00:15:31,080 --> 00:15:34,650
I've been having so much school work lately that I have no time for anything else.

206
00:15:34,650 --> 00:15:36,420
Yeah, right.

207
00:15:36,420 --> 00:15:40,530
Seriously. Plus, I know you joined Mingyuan. You must have been busy,

208
00:15:40,530 --> 00:15:42,240
so I didn't want to distract you.

209
00:15:42,240 --> 00:15:44,940
I may be busy, but I'll never be as busy as your President Tang.

210
00:15:44,940 --> 00:15:49,400
When Director Xia went missing, your President Tang had to work all day and all night for a few days.

211
00:15:49,400 --> 00:15:53,930
He is visibly emaciated. It must make you feel awful.

212
00:15:53,930 --> 00:15:56,520
When did Director Xia go missing?

213
00:15:56,520 --> 00:15:58,360
Did President Tang not tell you?

214
00:15:58,360 --> 00:16:01,620
Just a few days before the new recruits came in.

215
00:16:01,620 --> 00:16:05,410
He never talks to me about work.

216
00:16:05,410 --> 00:16:07,520
Has Mingyuan recruited more people?

217
00:16:07,520 --> 00:16:10,440
Yes, a man called...

218
00:16:10,440 --> 00:16:13,160
Cheng Yang. He recently came back from Paris.

219
00:16:13,160 --> 00:16:16,570
President Tang didn't say it out loud, but everyone knows

220
00:16:16,570 --> 00:16:19,440
he might replace Director Xia.

221
00:16:19,440 --> 00:16:22,610
I guess Director Xia thinks so, too.

222
00:16:22,610 --> 00:16:24,930
So she has been extra strict lately, just to show how important she is.

223
00:16:24,930 --> 00:16:29,320
The designers have been so busy.

224
00:16:29,320 --> 00:16:32,450
To think such a high-powered woman

225
00:16:32,450 --> 00:16:34,690
also feels insecure.

226
00:16:34,690 --> 00:16:39,360
Maybe Director Xia is overthinking it. It could be just a normal change with personnel.

227
00:16:39,360 --> 00:16:41,260
I think she is overthinking it, too.

228
00:16:41,260 --> 00:16:44,780
I heard President Tang personally talked to her to get her to come back

229
00:16:44,780 --> 00:16:47,520
just so she will feel comfortable working here.

230
00:16:47,520 --> 00:16:50,290
That could be his way of telling the world that Director Xia is his right-hand man,

231
00:16:50,290 --> 00:16:54,550
no matter who comes along.

232
00:16:55,250 --> 00:16:57,520
I don't get it.

233
00:16:57,520 --> 00:17:01,140
Go ask President Tang. Someone is here. Got to go.

234
00:17:01,140 --> 00:17:04,530
You are not the manager. What do you have to worry about?

235
00:17:10,720 --> 00:17:13,160
Which one do I choose?

236
00:17:14,860 --> 00:17:17,540
What's this product like?

237
00:17:19,440 --> 00:17:21,770
It has some very good reviews.

238
00:17:21,770 --> 00:17:23,440
Let's order some.

239
00:17:25,470 --> 00:17:27,320
What about this one?

240
00:17:28,840 --> 00:17:31,560
Its country of origin and raw material...

241
00:17:31,560 --> 00:17:33,520
Reviews.

242
00:17:37,450 --> 00:17:39,520
Get some of those as well.

243
00:17:39,520 --> 00:17:41,920
Get it done now. Go.

244
00:17:50,120 --> 00:17:53,140
- Who is it?
- Delivery!

245
00:17:57,740 --> 00:18:00,180
- Miss Mo Fei?
- Yes.

246
00:18:00,180 --> 00:18:02,900
This is a package from China.

247
00:18:03,520 --> 00:18:06,420
- Thank you.
- I hope you have a good day.

248
00:18:06,420 --> 00:18:08,890
- Bye!
- Bye!

249
00:18:20,980 --> 00:18:23,160
Mingxuan?

250
00:18:26,290 --> 00:18:29,280
You've just moved in and yet you are already receiving packages.

251
00:18:30,080 --> 00:18:31,270
What is it?

252
00:18:31,270 --> 00:18:34,360
I don't know. Let's see.

253
00:18:34,360 --> 00:18:36,170
Careful.

254
00:18:46,420 --> 00:18:49,000
Soft. What is it?

255
00:18:49,000 --> 00:18:53,350
Ju Hong Gao, a snack from Zhejiang.

256
00:18:57,400 --> 00:19:01,040
This one is Yun Pian Gao. I've tasted it before.

257
00:19:01,040 --> 00:19:02,660
Who sent you all these?

258
00:19:02,660 --> 00:19:04,930
Your President Tang?

259
00:19:06,720 --> 00:19:08,920
